cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a framework for evaluating multimodal deep learning models with respect to their language understanding and generalization abilities. The paper focuses on visual question answering models and generates artificial data to control the content of the data during training and evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves deep learning models, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as likely sub-categories.
